'''Love''' is a profound [[feeling]] of tender [[affection]] for or intense [[interpersonal attraction|attraction]] to another. It is considered a deep, ineffable feeling shared in passionate or [[intimacy|intimate]] [[interpersonal relationship]]s. However, in different contexts, the word ''love'' has a variety of related but distinct meanings: in addition to [[romantic love]], which is a mix of [[emotion]]al and [[human sexuality|sexual]] desire, other forms include [[platonic love]], [[love (religious views)|religious love]], [[familial love]], and, more casually, a feeling of pleasure, joy, or desire for something, even activities and foods. This diverse range of meanings in a single word is commonly contrasted with the plurality of [[Greek words for love|Greek words for ''Love'']], reflecting the word's versatility and complexity.
